OL,3,CTop Welsh GCSE results fall and still
OL,4,Clower than pre-pandemic levels
OL,6,FThe number of pupils in Wales
OL,7,Fachieving the top grades (A*-A) has
OL,8,Ffallen on last year and is still lower
OL,9,Fthan pre-pandemic figures.
OL,11,FIn comparison to 2024 UK-wide figures,
OL,12,Fthe highest grades are also lower than
OL,13,Flast year but higher than 2019.
OL,15,FOver 58,000 learners in Wales received
OL,16,Ftheir GCSE results at schools and
OL,17,Fcolleges across the nation today.
